Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AIPlayer
    Represents an AI Player, with 4 options for selecting moves.
    AITests
    Unit tests used throughout development of the AI class, for testing of each strategy.
    Board
    Represents an Amazons board, storing its shape, as well as each of the squares associated with it.
    BoardPartitionSetup
    Used to store information about how a board partitions shape and what squares are burnt / contain pieces.
    BoardTests
    Unit tests used throughout development of the board class, allowing for testing of its methods.
    DatabaseFiller
    Used to fill the Endgame Database with GameValues for all possible boards up to a specified size, in a systematic way to ensure that we have as quick an AI as possible at run-time.
    DatabaseTests
    Unit tests used to test connecting to and using the endgame database.
    FileInputOutput
    File input/output for both saved games in GameFile objects, as well as the Endgame Database, a mapping of boards hashcodes to evaluated GameValue objects.
    GameEngine
    Used to run the Amazons program, containing methods to play the game, simulate games, as well the tutorial and review game options.
    GameFile
    Stores a previously played game, with the moves played and board size, allowing the game to be stored in a file, as well as reviewed later.
    GameFileWriterReader  
    GameValue
    Represents the value of a particular position in a game.
    GameValueTests
    Unit tests used throughout development of the GameValue class, allowing for testing of its methods.
    HumanPlayer
    Represents a human player, allowing a program user to select moves, as well as validating the positions selected are valid.
    IO
    Used for getting all input from the user, including setup and playing of games, navigating the tutorial, reviewing of games, and choosing partitions to simulate.
    MCTS
    Monte-Carlo Tree Search algorithm implementation
    Move
    Represents a move that is played in the Amazons game, containing information about the player who played the move, as well as the starting square, finishing square, square that was shot, and the piece that was used.
    Piece
    Represents a piece in the Amazons game, storing both the colour and the position on the board that the piece is currently located.
    Player
    Represents a player for the Amazons game, acting as a superclass that both the AI and human players inherit from.
    ReportExamples
    Used to print examples of aspects of the program working correctly for the implementation section of the report.
    SimulatePartitions
    Used throughout development to test how different partitions favour black or white, via simulations.
    Square
    Represents a Square on a board, containing information about its location (x & y co-ordinate), if it contains an Amazon Piece, as well as if it is burnt
